________________________________________________________________________
special Permission 

chmod specialPermission owner group others file or directory name 

chmod 775 /data  ==> basic Permission without SUID SGID Sticky bit 

                OR 

chmod  0775 /data ==> basic Permission without SUID SGID Sticky bit

_________________________________________________________________________

1- SUID         ==> set user id or super user id   ==>  4 ==> u+s
2- SGID         ==> set group id or super group id ==>  2 ==> g+s
3- Sticky Bit   ==> Sticky bit                     ==>  1 ==> o+t

_________________________________________________________________________

drwxrwxrwx  ==> directory

x replaced by s in user  block : so SUID
x replaced by s in group block : so GUID
x replaced by t in other block : so sticky bit 
drwsrwsrwt  

d rws   rws   rwt
  SUID  SGID  StickyBit 
_________________________________________________________________________

when you will check below one , color will be different 
[root@rhel9-1 ~]# ls -l /usr/bin/su
-rwsr-xr-x. 1 root root 69016 Aug 24  2022 /usr/bin/su

_________________________________________________________________________
 now lets understand one thing SUID , SGID and sticky bit command can be applied on all three
 command , files or directory but we need 


 Permission          command          Files        directory

 SUID                 OK              X             X

 SGID                 X               X             OK

 sticky Bit           X               X             OK

 17:09
